$ZIM going through foreign tax credits with one of my clients who owns ZIM really shows me why so many people are avoiding ZIM in North America.  In Canada you get a 15 percent foreign tax credit but the actual dividend is taxed as income.  If it’s in a registers account you lose the tax deferral.  It’s a literal disaster for individual shareholders.   All these newbies are going to get a tax and dividend lesson in the future
